('2025-04-26-cryptocurrency-trade-war', 17, 'multiple_choice', 'Government', 'What oversight mechanisms exist for cryptocurrency regulatory agencies?', 'No oversight of crypto regulators', 'Congressional oversight, inspector generals, and judicial review', 'Only internal agency oversight', 'Complete regulatory independence', 'Congressional oversight, inspector generals, and judicial review', 'Multiple oversight mechanisms ensure regulatory accountability.', 'Oversight of cryptocurrency regulatory agencies includes congressional hearings and investigations, inspector general reviews of agency actions, judicial review of regulatory decisions, and public accountability measures to ensure appropriate exercise of regulatory authority.', '["congressional oversight", "inspector general", "judicial review"]', '[{"name": "Government Accountability Office", "url": "https://www.gao.gov/"}, {"name": "House Financial Services Committee", "url": "https://financialservices.house.gov/"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - Regulatory Oversight", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R45427"}]'),

