('2025-04-26-cryptocurrency-trade-war', 23, 'short_answer', 'Constitutional Law', 'What constitutional provision gives Congress authority to regulate digital currencies?', '', '', '', '', 'Commerce Clause', 'This provision in Article I grants Congress broad economic regulatory power.', 'The Commerce Clause in Article I, Section 8 gives Congress constitutional authority to regulate digital currencies by controlling interstate and international commerce. Congress also has power to coin money and regulate its value.', '["Commerce Clause", "Article I powers", "constitutional authority"]', '[{"name": "Constitution - Article I Powers", "url": "https://constitution.congress.gov/browse/article-1/section-8/"}, {"name": "Supreme Court - Commerce Clause Cases", "url": "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/commerce-clause/"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - Constitutional Digital Currency Authority", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R45427"}]'),

('2025-04-26-cryptocurrency-trade-war', 24, 'short_answer', 'Government', 'What federal agency enforces economic sanctions on cryptocurrency transactions?', '', '', '', '', 'Treasury Department', 'The Treasury\'s OFAC division administers and enforces economic sanctions.', 'The Treasury Department, specifically through the Office of Foreign Assets Control (OFAC), enforces economic sanctions on cryptocurrency transactions, prohibiting crypto dealings with sanctioned individuals, entities, and countries.', '["Treasury Department", "OFAC", "sanctions enforcement"]', '[{"name": "Treasury - OFAC", "url": "https://home.treasury.gov/policy-issues/office-of-foreign-assets-control-sanctions-programs-and-information"}, {"name": "Financial Crimes Enforcement Network", "url": "https://www.fincen.gov/"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - Sanctions Enforcement", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R45427"}]'),

('2025-04-26-cryptocurrency-trade-war', 25, 'short_answer', 'Economy', 'What does CBDC stand for in digital currency policy?', '', '', '', '', 'Central Bank Digital Currency', 'This refers to government-issued digital currencies backed by central banks.', 'CBDC stands for Central Bank Digital Currency, which refers to digital forms of government-issued currency that would be backed and controlled by central banks like the Federal Reserve, potentially competing with private cryptocurrencies.', '["CBDC", "Central Bank Digital Currency", "government digital money"]', '[{"name": "Federal Reserve - CBDC", "url": "https://www.federalreserve.gov/central-bank-digital-currency.htm"}, {"name": "Bank for International Settlements - CBDCs", "url": "https://www.bis.org/topics/central_bank_digital_currencies.htm"}, {"name": "Congressional Research Service - CBDC Explained", "url": "https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/R/R45427"}]');